e="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The importance of public access to the countryside is well rehearsed.</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Rights of Way offer everyone the opportunity to explore and enjoy the countryside, providing a key role in contributing to national agendas such as health and wellbeing, sustainable transport and rural economic growth.</span></li><li style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The Definitive Map and Statement of public rights of way provides the foundation for this network of access. An accurate and up to date definitive map is vital in providing clear information to users of the countryside and clarity and certain</span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">ty</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> for those who own and manage the land.</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> The present process for making changes to this legal record is lengthy, bureaucratic and often generates conflict.</span></li><li style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">IPROW strongly supports the case for legislative reform of the processes for recording rights of way on the Definitive Map in England.</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> The package of proposals put forward by the Natural England convened Stakeholder Working Group on Public Rights of Way offers a sensible</span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">, balanced</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> approach to removing unnecessary bureaucracy and cost from the current system in a manner which is acceptable to stakeholders across the spectrum.</span></li><li style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Significant effort and negotiation has gone into producing a negotiated package of proposals that the various stakeholders support. </span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">As the body representing professionals employed in this field</span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> our particular interest is in getting a fair and workable amendment to the present processes.</span></li><li style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Whilst we welcome discussions with other parties with the aim of making minor improvements to the presently proposed package, we do not wish to see hard-won progress towards legislative reform undone by changes that alter the balance of the proposals</span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> so that they no longer command across the board support.</span></li><li style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We therefore fully support and endorse the submission made to this Committee by Ray Anderson, the Chairman of the Stakeholder Working Group and would be pleased to provide any further information that the Committee may require.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Richard Cuthbert</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Emma </span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Noyce</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">President</span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="color:#404040; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><